external_knowledge:
"Almost out of stock" refers to ingredient quantities that have reached or fallen below their predefined reorder threshold.;
"Critical low stock" implies the situation where the inventory quantity has hit the reorder level, necessitating a new order to prevent stockouts.;
"High and low usage quantities" refer to the maximum and minimum quantities of ingredients used in any single order for a given menu item.;

sql:
SELECT menu_item_id
FROM menu_item_locations
WHERE location_id = 1 AND availability = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Regular customers are those who have placed more than one order;
- 'Frequently ordered' implies these items have been ordered multiple times and in different quantities, hence the average quantity is computed;
- Only completed orders are considered for the calculation of average amounts.
